    <string name="leak_test_what_is_title">What is a DNS Leak?</string>
    <string name="leak_test_what_is_desc">A DNS leak occurs when your device sends DNS queries outside your secure DNS connection. This means your ISP or other third parties can see which websites you visit, even if you\'re using a private DNS server.</string>
    <string name="leak_test_why_matters_title">Why Does It Matter?</string>
    <string name="leak_test_why_matters_desc">DNS leaks expose your browsing history to your Internet Service Provider, who can log, sell, or share this data. It also allows network administrators, hackers, or governments to monitor your online activity.</string>
    <string name="leak_test_how_fix_title">How to Stay Protected</string>
    <string name="leak_test_how_fix_desc">Activate DNS Changer to route all your DNS queries through a secure server. Choose a trusted DNS provider and run this test regularly to ensure your DNS protection is working properly.</string>
